<paragraph blockId="3.[2063,2658,676,1100]" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2063,2218,676,705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas &amp; Wroughton, 1909" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1909" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">Miniopterus medius Thomas &amp; Wroughton, 1909</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="694">
“Kalipoetjang, Tji-Tandoei R[iver].,” 
<collectingRegion box="[2322,2384,755,784]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Java</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[2400,2541,755,784]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[2063,2658,676,1100]" lastBlockId="3.[1453,2665,1107,2798]" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1909" box="[2064,2321,790,823]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">Miniopterus medius</taxonomicName>
is not very clearly defined. It was suggested that it was close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonhote" authorityYear="1902" box="[2064,2196,873,902]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fuscus">M. fuscus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1909" box="[2219,2475,873,902]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">Miniopterus medius</taxonomicName>
is somehow a mixture of all species intermediate in size between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[2252,2358,948,981]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">australis</taxonomicName>
species complex and. Ee 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2065,2195,992,1021]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">schreibersii</taxonomicName>
complex; however, genetic information available on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1909" box="[2391,2526,1027,1060]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">M. medius</taxonomicName>
indicates that the situation might be as confusing as it is for other forms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1783,1936,1107,1140]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
. For example, mitochondrial sequences from 
<collectingCountry box="[2593,2656,1107,1140]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Laos</collectingCountry>
and Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[1679,1795,1146,1179]" name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
suggest that they represent two different cryptic species. Besides, two available mitochondrial sequences from New 
<collectingCountry box="[2231,2332,1194,1219]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="3" pageNumber="694">Guinea</collectingCountry>
are very different from each other, and one groups with M. tristisand the other closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[2335,2488,1225,1258]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="694" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">M. australis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="694" type="distribution">
